HIV/AIDS: China ta ba da rahoton karuwar kashi 14 cikin 100 na sababbin kamuwa da cutar
Kasar Sin ta sanar da cewa yawan mutanen da ke dauke da cutar HIV da AIDS ya karu da kashi 14 cikin 100.
Mutane fiye da 820,000 ne suka kamu da cutar a kasar, in ji jami'an lafiya.
An samu karin mutane 40,000 a cikin kashi na biyu na shekara ta 2018 kawai.
Yawancin sababbin cututtuka sun fito ne daga jima'i, wanda ya nuna canji daga abin da ya faru a baya.
A wasu wurare a ƙasar Sin, cutar HIV ta yi yaduwa sosai a sakamakon zubar da jini da aka yi wa mutane.
Amma, an rage yawan mutanen da suka kamu da cutar HIV a wannan hanyar zuwa kusan babu, in ji jami'an lafiya na kasar Sin a wani taro a lardin Yunnan.
Amma, a cikin wani yanayi na shekara-shekara, yawan mutanen da ke da HIV da AIDS a kasar Sin ya karu da mutane 100,000.
Yada HIV ta hanyar jima'i matsala ce mai tsanani a cikin al'ummar LGBT na kasar Sin.
An haramta jima'i a kasar Sin a shekara ta 1997, amma an ce ana nuna wariya ga LGBT.
Wasu bincike sun nuna cewa saboda ra'ayin da mutanen ƙasar suke da shi, kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin 100 na maza da suka yi jima'i da wasu maza sun auri mata.
Yawancin cututtuka na cututtuka sun fito ne daga rashin kariya ta jima'i a cikin waɗannan dangantaka.
Tun shekara ta 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samun damar yin amfani da maganin HIV a ko'ina a duniya a matsayin wani ɓangare na ƙoƙarin magance matsalar.
