Jakadan Amurka ya zargi kasar Sin da "karyar" da "tallace-tallace"
Wata mako bayan wata jaridar kasar Sin ta wallafa wani sanarwa mai shafuka hudu a cikin wata jaridar Amurka da ke tallata amfanin cinikin Amurka da China, jakadan Amurka a kasar Sin ya zargi Beijing da amfani da jaridar Amurka wajen yada labaran.
Shugaban Amurka Donald Trump ya yi nuni a ranar Laraba da takardar biyan kuɗi na China Daily a cikin Des Moines Register, jaridar da ta fi kowa buga a jihar Iowa, bayan ya zargi China da ƙoƙarin tsoma baki a zaben Majalisar Dinkin Duniya na 6 ga Nuwamba, zargin da China ta musanta.
Zargin da Trump ya yi cewa Beijing na kokarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka ya nuna farkon abin da jami'an Amurka, a cikin wata sanarwa ga Reuters, suka kira sabon mataki a yakin neman zaben Washington na matsa lamba kan China.
Duk da yake yana da kyau gwamnatocin kasashen waje su buga tallace-tallace don inganta kasuwanci, Beijing da Washington a yanzu suna cikin ƙara rikitarwa a yaƙin kasuwanci wanda ya ga bangarorin biyu suna amfani da sassaucin haraji a kan shigo da kayayyakin juna.
An tsara kudaden da kasar Sin ta biya a farkon yakin kasuwanci don shafar masu fitar da kayayyaki a jihohin da ke goyon bayan Jam'iyyar Republican ta Trump, in ji masana na kasar Sin da na Amirka.
Terry Branstad, jakadan Amurka a kasar Sin kuma tsohon gwamnan Iowa, babban mai fitar da kayayyakin gona zuwa kasar Sin, ya ce Beijing ta yi wa ma'aikatan Amurka, manoma da kamfanoni lahani.
Branstad ya rubuta a wata kasida a cikin jaridar Des Moines Register a ranar Lahadi cewa, "yanzu kasar Sin tana saka hannu a cikin wannan barazanar ta hanyar wallafa tallace-tallace a cikin jaridarmu".
Branstad ya ce: "Tare da wannan tarurrukan, gwamnatin Sin tana amfani da ƙaunataccen al'adar Amirka na 'yancin yin magana da kuma yin wa'azi ta wajen wallafa wani sanarwa a Des Moines Register da aka biya kuɗi".
Ya rubuta: "A wajen bankuna a nan Beijing, mun ga ƙarancin muryoyin masu son ra'ayi kuma ba za mu taɓa ganin ainihin yadda 'yan kasar Sin za su nuna bambancin ra'ayi game da tattalin arzikin kasarsu ba, domin kafofin watsa labarai suna ƙarƙashin ikon jam'iyyar kwaminisancin kasar Sin".
Bugu da ƙari, ta ƙara da cewa "daya daga cikin manyan jaridu na kasar Sin ya ƙi yin tayin" ta buga labarinta, ko da yake bai ambata wanda ba.
'Yan Republican sun ware mata daga zaben kafin zaben ta'addanci da bala'in Kavanaugh, masu bincike sun yi gargadin
A lokacin da manyan 'yan Republican ke goyon bayan kuma suke kare dan takarar Kotun Koli Brett Kavanaugh a kan zargin da ake yi masa na cin zarafin jima'i, masu bincike sun yi gargadin cewa hakan zai iya jawo mummunan martani, musamman ga mata, a lokacin zaben da za a yi nan gaba.
A halin yanzu dai, an yi ta daɗaɗaɗa da tashin hankali a kan batun, kuma yawancin 'yan Republican sun riga sun bayyana a fili cewa suna son su yi zabe.
Wannan ba shi da wani abin da zai iya komawa baya", in ji Grant Reeher, wani farfesa a makarantar siyasa a Jami'ar Syracuse, don wani labarin da aka wallafa a ranar Asabar.
Reeher ya ce yana shakkar cewa matsa lamba daga Sanata Jeff Flake (Jam'iyyar Republican daga Arizona) don gudanar da binciken FBI zai isa ya kwantar da hankalin masu jefa kuri'a.
"Mata ba za su manta da abin da ya faru a jiya ba - ba za su manta da gobe ba ko a watan Nuwamba ba", in ji Karine Jean-Pierre, babban mai ba da shawara da kuma kakakin kasa na ƙungiyar masu ci gaba da motsawa, a ranar Jumma'a, a cewar jaridar Washington, D.C.
A safiyar Juma'a, 'yan Protestant suna rera "Litinin ya yi kusa!" a lokacin da suke zanga-zangarsu a cikin gidan majalisar dattijai, tun da 'yan Republican da ke kula da Kwamitin Shari'a suka zaɓi su ci gaba da zaben Kavanaugh duk da shaidar Dr. Christine Blasey Ford, in ji Mic.
"Himma da kuma himmar 'yan Democrat za su ci dukan tarihi", in ji Stu Rothenberg, wani mai bincike a kan siyasa da ba shi da wani ɓangare na jam'iyyar.
"Mutane suna cewa ta yi girma, kuma hakan gaskiya ne.
Amma zai iya zama mafi girma, musamman tsakanin masu jefa kuri'a da ba su yanke shawara ba a yankunan birane da kuma matasa masu jefa kuri'a, masu shekaru 18 zuwa 29, waɗanda ko da yake ba sa son shugaban kasa, sau da yawa ba sa jefa kuri'a".
Kafin shaidar Ford ta bayyana zargin ta da cin zarafin da ya yi wa wanda aka nada a kotun koli, masu bincike sun nuna cewa za a iya samun mummunan sakamako idan 'yan Republican suka ci gaba da tabbatarwa.
"Wannan ya zama abin takaici ga Jam'iyyar Republican", in ji Michael Steele, tsohon shugaban kwamitin jam'iyyar Republican a farkon makon da ya gabata, a cewar NBC News.
Guy Cecil, darektan kungiyar da ke taimakawa wajen zaben 'yan Democrat, Priorities USA, ya gaya wa kamfanin labarai cewa: "Ba wai kawai game da zaben da kwamitin ya yi ba ne, ko kuma ko Kavanaugh zai yi aiki a matsayin alƙali, amma kuma game da yadda 'yan Republican suka bi da batun da kuma yadda suka bi da shi".
Amma, a Amirka, mutane sun nuna cewa sun rabu game da wanda za su gaskata bayan shaidar Ford da Kavanaugh, kuma ƙaramin rinjaye ya amince da wannan.
Wani sabon binciken da YouGov ya yi ya nuna cewa kashi 41 cikin 100 na mutanen da aka bincika sun yi imani da shaidar Ford ko kuma sun yi imani da ita, yayin da kashi 35 cikin 100 suka ce sun yi imani da Kavanaugh ko kuma sun yi imani da shi.
Bugu da ƙari, kashi 38 cikin ɗari sun ce sun yi imanin cewa Kavanaugh ya yi ƙarya ko kuma ya yi ƙarya a shaidarsa, yayin da kashi 30 cikin ɗari ne kawai suka ce haka game da Ford.
Bayan Flake ya yi hakan, FBI ta fara bincike kan zargin Ford da kuma wani mai tuhumarsa, Deborah Ramirez, kamar yadda jaridar Guardian ta ruwaito.
