Tom Daley ya ji "ƙananan" game da jima'i
Dan wasan Olympic mai suna Tom Daley ya ce ya girma yana jin cewa ya kasa kowa saboda jima'i, amma hakan ya ba shi dalili ya zama mai nasara.
Dan wasan mai shekara 24 ya ce bai fahimci hakan ba sai da ya shiga makarantar sakandare cewa "ba kowa ba ne kamar ni".
A wata hira da aka yi da gidan rediyo na farko na Desert Island Discs wanda Lauren Laverne ya gabatar, ya ce ya yi magana a madadin 'yancin 'yan luwadi don ba da " bege " ga wasu.
Ya kuma ce zama uba ya sa ya damu da samun nasara a gasar Olympics.
Kirsty Young, wadda ta daɗe tana gabatar da wannan shirin, ta yi hutu na watanni da yawa saboda rashin lafiya.
Da yake bayyana a matsayin ɗan wasa a shirin farko na Laverne, Daley ya ambata cewa ya ji "ƙananan" ga dukan sauran saboda "ba a yarda da shi a zamantakewar jama'a ba don son yara maza da mata".
A cikin kalmominsa, "har zuwa yau, wannan tunanin cewa muna jin ƙanƙanta da kuma bambanci ya kasance ainihin dalilin da ya ba ni iko da ƙarfin yin nasara".
Ya ce manufarsa ita ce ta tabbatar da cewa shi "wani ne", don kada kowa ya yi sanyin gwiwa sa'ad da suka gano jima'i.
Dan wasan da ya lashe lambar tagulla ta Olympics sau biyu ya zama babban mai ba da agaji ga LGBT kuma ya yi amfani da halartar gasar Commonwealth Games na wannan shekara a Ostiraliya don ya yi kira ga wasu ƙasashe su kawar da cin zarafin 'yan luwadi.
Ya ce ya bayyana kansa domin yana farin ciki da ya yi rayuwa a sarari ba tare da sakamako ba kuma yana son ya ba da " bege " ga wasu.
Dan wasan duniya mai nasara uku ya ce ya yi sha'awar wani mutum, dan wasan fim na Amurka Dustin Lance Black, wanda ya sadu da shi a shekara ta 2013, "ya mamaye ni".
Daley ta auri Oscar din da ya fi ta shekaru 20 da haihuwa a shekarar da ta gabata, ko da yake ta ce bambancin shekaru bai taba zama matsala ba.
"Sa'ad da muka sha wahala sosai a lokacin da muke ƙanana", - ya fara halartar gasar Olympics a shekara ta 14 kuma mahaifinsa ya rasu daga ciwon daji shekaru uku bayan haka - ya ce, yana da wuya a sami wani da ya yi irin wannan rayuwa.
A watan Yuni na bara, ma'auratan sun haifi ɗa, mai suna Robert Ray Black-Daley, kuma Daley ya ce "dukan ra'ayinsu" ya canja.
"Idan ka tambaye ni a bara, duk abin da ya fi muhimmanci shi ne samun lambar zinariya", in ji shi.
"Amma ka sani, akwai abubuwa da suka fi zinariya na Olympics girma.
"Lambar zinare ta Olympics ita ce Robbie".
Ɗansa yana da suna ɗaya da mahaifinsa Robert, wanda ya mutu a shekara ta 2011 yana da shekara 40 bayan an gano shi da ciwon daji a kwakwalwa.
Daley ya ce mahaifinsa bai yarda da cewa zai mutu ba kuma daya daga cikin abubuwan da ya yi tambaya na karshe shi ne ko sun riga sun samu tikiti zuwa wasannin London na 2012 domin yana son kasancewa a jere.
"Ba zan iya gaya masa ba cewa ba za ka kasance a nan don ka kasance a jere na farko, Baba", ya ce.
"Na riƙe hannunsa a lokacin da ya daina numfashi, kuma kawai lokacin da ya daina numfashi kuma ya mutu ne na fahimci cewa ba za a iya cin nasara da shi ba", in ji shi.
A shekara ta gaba, Daley ya yi gasar Olympics ta 2012 kuma ya lashe lambar tagulla.
"Na san cewa abin da na yi mafarki na yi a rayuwata: yin ruwa a gaban 'yan'uwa a gasar Olympics... babu abin da ya fi wannan".
Wannan kuma ya yi wahayi zuwa ga waƙar da ta fara zaɓa - Proud, ta Heather Small - wadda ta yi wa kanta alama a lokacin da take shirin halartar gasar Olympics, kuma har yanzu tana ba ta fata.
Desert Island Discs za ta fito a tashar rediyo ta BBC 4 a ranar Lahadi da misalin karfe 11:15 na yammacin Birtaniya.
